1769
01:41:38.380 --> 01:41:42.200
We collected the cells from tumor-bearing bones and then conducted

1770
01:41:42.320 --> 01:41:45.640
single cell profiling along with characterization of

1771
01:41:46.540 --> 01:41:47.740
cell surface antigen.

1772
01:41:48.900 --> 01:41:52.560
Using systemic cross-transcriptional comparisons

1773
01:41:52.640 --> 01:41:56.520
between the species, we found analogous mature neutrophils

1774
01:41:56.540 --> 01:42:00.300
in our intraosseous models. And consistent with human

1775
01:42:00.340 --> 01:42:04.280
data, our target neutrophils show elevated immune-suppressive

1776
01:42:04.300 --> 01:42:08.040
molecular programs, suggesting that these neutrophils are well

1777
01:42:08.080 --> 01:42:09.800
recapitulated in our model.

1778
01:42:12.300 --> 01:42:16.240
Using cell surface markers revealed by our multi-omics

1779
01:42:16.280 --> 01:42:19.800
sequencing, including CD62L and CXCR2,

1780
01:42:20.360 --> 01:42:23.760
we successfully confirmed their presence at protein levels.

1781
01:42:24.700 --> 01:42:28.540
To test whether they are immunosuppressive, we isolated these

1782
01:42:28.580 --> 01:42:32.180
neutrophils and co-cultured them with activated

1783
01:42:32.240 --> 01:42:33.280
CD8 T cells.

1784
01:42:34.200 --> 01:42:38.049
The horizontal axis represents proliferation of T cells, and

1785
01:42:38.120 --> 01:42:41.660
we found that these neutrophils potently suppress T cell

1786
01:42:41.940 --> 01:42:45.300
proliferation and activation, at least in culture.

1787
01:42:47.440 --> 01:42:51.100
